# ─── profiles/common.env ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canonical, DOCUMENTED values for the llama.cpp vision-server knobs that are
# IDENTICAL on every machine (cosmic, cosmos, any future box). These are the
# benchmarked production defaults — change a shared knob HERE, in one place.
#
# CONSUMPTION — honest status as of 2026-06-27 (do not overstate this file):
#   • scripts/cosmic/transcribe_vision.sh  DOES read LLAMACPP_MODEL from here.
#   • The server launchers do NOT yet source this file:
#       - scripts/cosmic/serve_vision.cmd  hardcodes NP/UBATCH/ctx/ngl/flash.
#       - scripts/llamacpp_server.sh        uses its own MODEL/PORT/CTX defaults.
#     So today these keys are the single source of TRUTH (documentation), not yet
#     the single source of CONSUMPTION. Wiring both launchers to read this file is
#     tracked future work; until then, keep the launchers' literals in sync with
#     the values below.
#
# What VARIES per machine (GPU backend, parallel slots, lib path, host) is NOT
# here — it lives in profiles/<machine>.env. See docs/reference/multi-machine-setup.md.
#
# Plain KEY=value, no quotes/spaces, so bash (`. file`) sources it directly.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LLAMACPP_MODEL=qwen2.5vl:7b
LLAMACPP_PORT=18082
LLAMACPP_CTX_PER_SLOT=8192
LLAMACPP_NGL=99
LLAMACPP_FLASH=on
LLAMACPP_BATCH=2048
LLAMACPP_UBATCH=2048
